definition.value: A tetrahydroxyflavone that is isoorientin in which the phenolic hydrogens at positions 3' and 7 have been replaced by methyl groups.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-SKF 38393
Any EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of a Ca(2+)/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase (EC 2.7.11.17).
A dopamine agonist that binds to and activates the dopamine receptor D1.
A 1-phenyl-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1H-3-benzazepine-7,8-diol that is the S-enantiomer of SKF 38393.
A peptide anion obtained by deprotonation of the the three carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of S-(2-carboxy-2-methylbut-3-en-2-yl)-glutathione; major species at pH 7.3.
An S-substituted glutathione(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the the two carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of S-(2-formyl-2-methylbut-3-en-2-yl)-glutathione; major species at pH 7.3.
Any cholestane ester carrying at least one hydroxy substituent.
A 1-phenyl-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1H-3-benzazepine-7,8-diol that is the R-enantiomer of SKF 38393.
A benzazepine that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-3-benzazepine bearing a phenyl substituent at position 1 and two hydroxy substituents at positions 7 and 8.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-SKF 38393 hydrobromide.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from L-allysine.
A hydrobromide obtained by combining (S)-SKF 38393 with one molar equivalent of hydrogen bromide.
A hydrobromide obtained by combining (R)-SKF 38393 with one molar equivalent of hydrogen bromide.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of (R)-SKF 38393.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of (S)-SKF 38393.
A nucleoside analogue obtained by formal cyclodimerisation of thymidine.
An agonist that enhances the action of smoothened (SMO) receptor.
A cyclobutadipyrimidine bis(deoxyribonucleotide) obtained by formal cyclodimerisation of thymidine 5'-monophosphate.
An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the N-sulfo group of any sulfamic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of any methylated primary amine; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of cyclobutadipyrimidines that is hexahydro-1,3,6,8-tetraazabiphenylene-2,4,5,7-tetrone carrying two additional methyl substituents at positions 4a and 4b.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound obtained by intramolecular formation of a C-C bond between positions 8 and 5' of 2'-deoxyadenosine.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound obtained by intramolecular formation of a C-C bond between positions 8 and 5' of dAMP.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound obtained by intramolecular formation of a C-C bond between positions 8 and 5' of 2'-deoxyguanosine.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound obtained by intramolecular formation of a C-C bond between positions 8 and 5' of dGMP.
A 1,2-diglyceride in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (9Z)-hexadecenoyl.
A flavone C-glycoside consisting of isoscoparin having a 6-(E)-feruloylglucosyl residue attached at position 2''.
A 1,2-diglyceride in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (11Z)-octadecenoyl.
A 5'-phospho-(3'->5')-dinucleotide composed from two dAMP residues.
A flavone C-glycoside that is luteolin in which the hydrogen at position 2 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-arabinosyl residue.
An N-glycosyl compound that is a metabolite produced by the bacterium Mycoplasma genitalium.
A 7-deazaguanosine ribonucleoside that has 7-carbamoyl-7-deazaguanine as the nucleobase. It is present in archaeal tRNA and has also been found in bacterial DNA.
A labdane diterpenoid with formula C21H36O4, originally isolated from the seeds of Oryza sativa.
A flavone C-glycoside that is 7-O-methylapigenin in which the hydrogen at position 6 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An organic sodium salt resulting from the replacement of the proton from the carboxy group of dodecanoic acid by a sodium ion.
Any steroid acid anion based on a cholestane skeleton.
Any steroid acid anion based on a pregnane skeleton.
Any steroid acid anion based on a lanostane skeleton.

An ammonium betaine that is beta-alaninate in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a trimethylamino group. A clinically used cardioprotective drug that is used for treatment of heart failure, myocardial infarction, arrhythmia, atherosclerosis and diabetes.

An EC 1.14.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, incorporating 1 atom each of oxygen into both donors) inhibitor that interferes with the action of gamma-butyrobetaine dioxygenase (EC 1.14.11.1).
A glycol that is 2-methylpropane in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 1 and 2..
A hydroxyaldehyde that is isobutyraldehyde carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 2.
A  carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2,4-didehydro-3-deoxy-L-rhamnonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fotemustine. It is an alkylating agent used in the treatment of malignant melanoma.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-erythritol 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

A 39 amino acid porcine cathelicidin that is rich in proline and arginine residues. It plays a pivotal role in the innate immune defence of the pig against infections and exhibits antimicrobial and immunomodulatory activities.

A fluoroindole that is 6-fluoroindole in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a 2-(pyridin-3-yl)vinyl group (trans configuration). It is a selective inhibitor of tryptophan 2,3-dioxygenase (TDO), which directs the conversion of trypophan to kynurenin.

A member of the class of N-nitrosoureas that is ethyl diethylphosphonate in the hydrogen at position 1 of the ethyl group attached to the phosphorus has been replaced by a [(2-chloroethyl)(nitroso)carbamoyl]amino group.
A diethyl (1-{[(2-chloroethyl)(nitroso)carbamoyl]amino}ethyl)phosphonate that has R configuration.
